Secora Logo Secora is Norwegian government enterprise created in 2005 to perform construction work on water transport infrastructure, both sea lanes and ports. The company was originally part of Kystverket, that is responsible for water transport infrastructure. Secora is based in Svolvær and has 90 employees. Source
